A dust storm rages around them. With a fractured arm, Hiromi cannot work. His fellow crew members take on extra shifts. Dust is causing more problems than anticipated. The drill which has been erected to search for water is breaking down and wearing out faster than predicted. Another blow from Houston: the Chinese have discovered water. Samples are being tested. A huge dust storm with an electrostatic discharge fries the drill’s electronics. And the Chinese results come in: the sample is saltier than the Dead Sea. It is highly unlikely that this water could have supported life. United behind their commander, the crew makes a request of the world’s leaders – allow us to use the Chinese drill to complete our mission.
